Q1. Why password is NOT stored in JWT?
👉 Because JWT is readable on client side; password must stay server-only.

Q2. Why we still query DB after verifying token?
👉 Because token proves identity, DB proves user still exists / is valid.

Q3. What breaks if middleware is removed?
👉 Anyone can access protected routes without login.

Q4. 401 vs 403?
👉 401 = not logged in, 403 = logged in but not allowed.

