Q1. Why password is NOT stored in JWT?

❌ “JWT readable on client”
✅ Correct:

JWT is stored on client and sent with every request.
Storing password would leak credentials if token is compromised.

Q2. Why we still query DB after verifying token?

❌ “check user existing or not” (too weak)
✅ Correct:

Because token only proves identity, not current validity.
User may be deleted, blocked, or role-changed.

This is VERY important. Seniors judge this answer.

